Karsch, 1881
</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName id="94814D3EFFF4E16CEF1BFE36FB00A4DF" authority="(Grube, 1873)" baseAuthorityName="Grube" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[830,1275,444,467]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scrobiculosus">
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF4E16CEF1BFE36FBA1A4DF" box="[830,1114,444,467]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Orthochirus scrobiculosus</emphasis>
(Grube, 1873)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="533E36BDFFF4E16CEF1BFE70FADDA1FD" blockId="10.[830,1441,506,1265]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<materialsCitation id="E3E93CE0FFF4E16CEF1BFE70FAD9A1FD" collectionCode="VI, IV, V" collectorName="Pectines &amp; Basal &amp; Males &amp; Hemispermatophore &amp; Sternum &amp; Tibial &amp; Cheliceral &amp; Carapace &amp; Pedipalp &amp; Tergites I &amp; Stigmata &amp; Metasomal &amp; Telson" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" specimenCode="V2, V1" specimenCount="1">
D IAGNOSIS. Total length under 
<quantity id="94799B58FFF4E16CE8E0FE70FADAA71D" box="[1221,1313,506,529]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="60.0">60 mm</quantity>
. Pedipalps orthobothriotaxic 
<typeStatus id="8C3A881FFFF4E16CE824FD92FBD4A723" box="[1025,1071,536,559]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
A (Vachon, 1974); dorsal trichobothria of femur arranged in 
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF4E16CE8A9FDBDFB62A742" box="[1164,1177,567,590]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">β</emphasis>
-configuration (Vachon, 1 975); trichobothrium 
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF4E16CE865FDDCFBB6A761" box="[1088,1101,598,621]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">d</emphasis>
<subScript id="CF0534F8FFF4E16CE868FDEAFBADA763" attach="left" box="[1101,1110,608,623]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">2</subScript>
of femur present or absent, either internal or external to dorsointernal carina; 
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF4E16CE94FFDFEFA8CA787" box="[1386,1399,628,651]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">d</emphasis>
<subScript id="CF0534F8FFF4E16CE952FDF4FA7BA781" attach="left" box="[1399,1408,638,653]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">3</subScript>
of femur internal to dorsomedian carina, when carina present; 
<specimenCode id="03279EC6FFF4E16CEF84FD38FC41A7C7" box="[929,954,690,715]" collectionCode="V" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" type="Museum">
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF4E16CEF84FD38FC4AA7C5" box="[929,945,690,713]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">V</emphasis>
<subScript id="CF0534F8FFF4E16CEF94FD36FC41A7C7" attach="left" box="[945,954,700,715]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">2</subScript>
</specimenCode>
on chela manus located behind 
<specimenCode id="03279EC6FFF4E16CE91EFD38FAAFA7C7" box="[1339,1364,690,715]" collectionCode="V" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" type="Museum">
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF4E16CE91EFD38FAB0A7C5" box="[1339,1355,690,713]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">V</emphasis>
<subScript id="CF0534F8FFF4E16CE96EFD36FAAFA7C7" attach="left" box="[1355,1364,700,715]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">1</subScript>
</specimenCode>
; 
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF4E16CE94CFD38FA83A7C5" box="[1385,1400,690,713]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">it</emphasis>
on distal fixed finger. 
<collectorName id="FE74536BFFF4E16CE83CFD5AFB89A7EB" box="[1049,1138,720,743]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Pectines</collectorName>
with fulcra, hirsute. 
<collectorName id="FE74536BFFF4E16CE940FD5AFA5BA7EB" box="[1381,1440,720,743]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Basal</collectorName>
middle lamella of pectines in females not dilated. 
<collectorName id="FE74536BFFF4E16CE97AFD65FA5BA60A" box="[1375,1440,751,774]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Males</collectorName>
with genital papillae. 
<collectorName id="FE74536BFFF4E16CE81FFC84FAEFA629" box="[1082,1300,782,805]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Hemispermatophore</collectorName>
flagelliform with lobes of capsule in 3+1 configuration, basal lobe small, median lobe not fused to base of flagellum. 
<collectorName id="FE74536BFFF4E16CEF1BFCE0FC63A68D" box="[830,920,874,897]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Sternum</collectorName>
subpentagonal. 
<collectorName id="FE74536BFFF4E16CE873FCE0FB6DA68D" box="[1110,1174,874,897]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Tibial</collectorName>
spurs present on third and fourth legs. 
<collectorName id="FE74536BFFF4E16CEFD4FC02FBA4A693" box="[1009,1119,904,927]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Cheliceral</collectorName>
fixed finger with two ventral denticles, margins of fingers with standard pattern of buthid dentition (Vachon, 1963). 
<collectorName id="FE74536BFFF4E16CE895FC4CFAE8A6D1" box="[1200,1299,966,989]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Carapace</collectorName>
without distinct carinae, in lateral view distinctly inclined downward from median eyes to anterior margin. 
<collectorName id="FE74536BFFF4E16CE966FB89FA5BA116" box="[1347,1440,1027,1050]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Pedipalp</collectorName>
chela movable finger with distinct granules divided into 7–11 rows, with 2–5 subdistal granules. 
<collectorName id="FE74536BFFF4E16CE92EFBCAFA8DA15B" box="[1291,1398,1088,1111]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Tergites I</collectorName>
– 
<collectionCode id="3590AE78FFF4E16CE9A1FBCAFA5BA15B" box="[1412,1440,1088,1111]" country="Norway" name="Mykotektet, National Veterinary Institute" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">VI</collectionCode>
smooth to granulated with one indicated carina or acarinate. 
<collectorName id="FE74536BFFF4E16CEF97FBF4FBEAA199" box="[946,1041,1150,1173]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Stigmata</collectorName>
are narrow slits. 
<collectorName id="FE74536BFFF4E16CE8C5FBF4FAADA199" box="[1248,1366,1150,1173]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Metasomal</collectorName>
- I–II with carinae. 
<collectorName id="FE74536BFFF4E16CEFF5FB16FBBCA1BF" box="[976,1095,1180,1203]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Metasomal</collectorName>
segments 
<collectionCode id="3590AE78FFF4E16CE89CFB16FB2EA1BF" box="[1209,1237,1180,1203]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">IV</collectionCode>
– 
<collectionCode id="3590AE78FFF4E16CE8C6FB16FB0DA1BF" box="[1251,1270,1180,1203]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
ventrally punctate. 
<collectorName id="FE74536BFFF4E16CEF51FB31FC46A1DE" box="[884,957,1211,1234]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Telson</collectorName>
elongate, smooth, without subaculear tubercle, aculeus as long as, or longer than vesicle
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1B9B6536FFF4E16DEF1BFA9DFE1DA260" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="533E36BDFFF4E16DEF1BFA9DFE1DA260" blockId="10.[830,1441,1303,1909]" lastBlockId="11.[192,802,1688,1900]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
COMMENTS. 
<bibRefCitation id="37104B4CFFF4E16CEFE9FA9DFB39A022" author="KRAEPELIN" box="[972,1218,1303,1326]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" pagination="557 - 578" refId="ref13701" refString="KRAEPELIN, K. 1903. Scorpione und Solifugen Nordost-Afrikas, gesammelt 1900 und 1901 von Carlo Freiherrn von Erlanger und Oscar Neumann. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abtheilung fur Systematik, 18 (4 - 5): 557 - 578." type="journal article" year="1903">Kraepelin (1903: 563)</bibRefCitation>
cited 
<specimenCount id="4587FD34FFF4E16CE92FFA9DFA5BA022" box="[1290,1440,1303,1326]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="94814D3EFFF4E16CEF45FABCFBD6A041" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1882" box="[864,1069,1334,1357]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Butheolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aristidis">
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF4E16CEF45FABCFBD6A041" box="[864,1069,1334,1357]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Butheolus aristidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="94814D3EFFF4E16CE87EFABCFC7EA067" authority="(Simon, 1883))" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1883" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aristidis">
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF4E16CE87EFABCFAC4A041" box="[1115,1343,1334,1357]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Orthochirus aristidis</emphasis>
(Simon, 1883))
</taxonomicName>
collected in &quot; 
<collectingCountry id="2B96762DFFF4E16CE811FADEFB6BA067" box="[1076,1168,1364,1387]" name="Somalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Somalia</collectingCountry>
, Lasman, Febr. 1900&quot;; Werner (1916: 81) cited a juvenile from 
<collectingCountry id="2B96762DFFF4E16CE8DCFAF9FAADA086" box="[1273,1366,1395,1418]" name="Djibouti" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Djibouti</collectingCountry>
. These 
<specimenCount id="4587FD34FFF4E16CEF1BFA18FC25A0A5" box="[830,990,1426,1449]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
have not been recently revised and there is a possibility that the specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="2B96762DFFF4E16CE8C1FA3AFAC0A0CB" box="[1252,1339,1456,1479]" name="Somalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Somalia</collectingCountry>
could be a species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="94814D3EFFF4E16CE86AFA45FA5BA0EA" authority="Kovarik, 1998" authorityName="Kovarik, Pakistanorthochirus Lourenco" authorityYear="1998" box="[1103,1440,1487,1510]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochiroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF4E16CE86AFA45FB09A0EA" box="[1103,1266,1487,1510]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Orthochiroides</emphasis>
Kovařík, 1998
</taxonomicName>
which in 
<collectingCountry id="2B96762DFFF4E16CEF94FA64FBF3A309" box="[945,1032,1518,1541]" name="Somalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Somalia</collectingCountry>
is represented by the type species 
<taxonomicName id="94814D3EFFF4E16CEF1BF986FB0CA32F" authority="Kovarik, 1998" authorityName="Kovarik" authorityYear="1998" box="[830,1271,1548,1571]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochiroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vachoni">
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF4E16CEF1BF986FBBEA32F" box="[830,1093,1548,1571]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Orthochiroides vachoni</emphasis>
Kovařík, 1998
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="2B96762DFFF4E16CE928F986FA93A32F" box="[1293,1384,1548,1571]" name="Somalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Somalia</collectingCountry>
, Sar Uanle, about 
<quantity id="94799B58FFF4E16CEFF0F9A1FBE7A34E" box="[981,1052,1579,1602]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" unit="km" value="20.0">20 km</quantity>
south from Chisimaio, 
<geoCoordinate id="36B5507AFFF4E16CE902F9A1FA5BA34E" box="[1319,1440,1579,1602]" degrees="00" direction="south" minutes="29" orientation="latitude" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" precision="15" seconds="48" value="-0.49666664">00°29'48&quot;S</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="36B5507AFFF4E16CEF1BF9C0FC46A36D" box="[830,957,1610,1633]" degrees="42" direction="east" minutes="25" orientation="longitude" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" precision="15" seconds="30" value="42.425003">42°25'30&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
). In contrast, the occurence of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="94814D3EFFF4E16CEF1BF9E2FC3AA373" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1892" box="[830,961,1640,1663]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF4E16CEF1BF9E2FC3AA373" box="[830,961,1640,1663]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Orthochirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="2B96762DFFF4E16CEFCDF9E2FBBAA373" box="[1000,1089,1640,1663]" name="Djibouti" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Djibouti</collectingCountry>
is expected, but this population is most probably not 
<taxonomicName id="94814D3EFFF4E16CE816F90DFB54A392" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[1075,1199,1671,1694]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aristidis">
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF4E16CE816F90DFB54A392" box="[1075,1199,1671,1694]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">O. aristidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Lourenço &amp; Leguin (2011: 1–4, 13, 14, 15, figs. 1–4, 22, 27, 33) published a redescription of 
<taxonomicName id="94814D3EFFF4E16CEFD1F94EFB94A3D7" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[1012,1135,1732,1755]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aristidis">
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF4E16CEFD1F94EFB94A3D7" box="[1012,1135,1732,1755]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">O. aristidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the 
<typeStatus id="8C3A881FFFF4E16CE92BF94EFA8BA3D7" box="[1294,1392,1732,1755]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">lectotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="8C3A881FFFF4E16CEF1BF969FC23A3F6" box="[830,984,1763,1786]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
from Nubia (
<collectingCountry id="2B96762DFFF4E16CE849F969FB55A3F6" box="[1132,1198,1763,1786]" name="Egypt" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Egypt</collectingCountry>
/ 
<collectingCountry id="2B96762DFFF4E16CE893F969FB00A3F6" box="[1206,1275,1763,1786]" name="Sudan" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Sudan</collectingCountry>
), near the Nile, and a topotype female collected in 
<collectingCountry id="2B96762DFFF4E16CE89FF888FB06A215" box="[1210,1277,1794,1817]" name="Sudan" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Sudan</collectingCountry>
(Nubia), Wadi Halfa, 
<date id="273F107DFFF4E16CEFAAF8AAFC18A23B" box="[911,995,1824,1847]" bridgedPair="/" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" value="1975-10">X/1975</date>
. They also published a photo of live female from 
<collectingCountry id="2B96762DFFF4E16CEFEEF8B5FBDFA25A" box="[971,1060,1855,1878]" name="Djibouti" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Djibouti</collectingCountry>
(Lourenço &amp; Leguin, 2011: 4, fig. 5) without information about whether the specimen was only photographed, or was collected, studied and compared to the types. Lourenço &amp; Leguin (2011: 3) also presumed that 
<taxonomicName id="94814D3EFFF5E16DED42F95DFE1FA3E2" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[359,484,1751,1774]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aristidis">
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF5E16DED42F95DFE1FA3E2" box="[359,484,1751,1774]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">O. aristidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could occur in 
<collectingCountry id="2B96762DFFF5E16DEEBAF95DFD02A3E2" box="[671,761,1751,1774]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
although no 
<taxonomicName id="94814D3EFFF5E16DED1FF97CFE47A201" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1892" box="[314,444,1782,1805]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF5E16DED1FF97CFE47A201" box="[314,444,1782,1805]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Orthochirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="2B96762DFFF5E16DEE23F97CFD9BA201" box="[518,608,1782,1805]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
was cited before this paper (Kovařík, 2003: 135). The types of 
<taxonomicName id="94814D3EFFF5E16DEE88F89CFD01A221" authority="Kovařík &amp; Lowe &amp; Šťáhlavský, 2016" authorityName="Kovařík &amp; Lowe &amp; Šťáhlavský" authorityYear="2016" box="[685,762,1814,1837]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afar" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF5E16DEE88F89CFD01A221" box="[685,762,1814,1837]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">O. afar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7AC657D4FFF5E16DEF27F89CFF2DA240" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" rank="species">
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF5E16DEF27F89CFCE0A221" bold="true" box="[770,795,1814,1837]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF5E16DECE5F8BFFF34A240" bold="true" box="[192,207,1845,1868]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
represent the first verified record of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="94814D3EFFF5E16DECE5F8DFFEB8A260" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1892" box="[192,323,1877,1900]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="61F5EAAFFFF5E16DECE5F8DFFEB8A260" box="[192,323,1877,1900]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Orthochirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="2B96762DFFF5E16DEDA6F8DFFE1AA260" box="[387,481,1877,1900]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
